Implementation Plan: PremiumShop AI Ecommerce Platform
PremiumShop AI is an enterprise-grade, highly scalable multi-category ecommerce web application built with Django, Django REST Framework, PostgreSQL, Redis, Celery, and a premium modern frontend using Tailwind CSS.

This document outlines the detailed architectural blueprints, database schemas, URL routing structures, payment flows, and deployment configurations to ensure the project meets the highest standards of code quality and user experience.

User Review Required
We propose using a modern Tailwind CSS + HTML5/ES6 + HTMX stack for the frontend. This allows us to achieve a premium UI/UX (comparable to Nike Store, Apple Store, and Amazon) with smooth interactive elements (like slide-out carts, dynamic filters, and real-time checkout updates) without the overhead of a heavy single-page application framework (like React or Vue), which often degrades SEO.

IMPORTANT

Tailwind CSS Version: We will use Tailwind CSS v3.4 via its official standalone CLI/CDN configuration for development, with transition hooks and Custom Vanilla CSS utility classes for rich gradients, glassmorphism, and dark/light modes.

Mock Integrations: For Cash on Delivery (COD), Stripe, and Razorpay, we will implement full backend controllers and success/failure webhook handling. In the local development sandbox, these will default to testing credentials or a mock simulator so you can verify the entire checkout loop without setting up live developer accounts.

Database Configuration: By default, the application will attempt to connect to PostgreSQL if environment variables are provided in .env. If not, it will seamlessly fall back to SQLite for instant local development, ensuring developers can spin up the application with a single python manage.py migrate command.

