Component Details & Database Schemas
We will define Django models with explicit database indexes (db_index=True), unique constraints (UniqueConstraint), and standard relation names (related_name).

1. Database Schema (models.py layouts)
[NEW] 
accounts/models.py
User: Custom user extending AbstractUser. Uses email as the username field.
Profile: One-to-one relationship with User. Stores phone number, profile image, wallet balance (DecimalField), and loyalty points.
Address: Foreign key to User. Fields: recipient_name, phone_number, street_address, city, state, postal_code, country (default 'IN'), address_type (Home/Work), and is_default (BooleanField).
[NEW] 
products/models.py
Category: Hierarchical model (parent FK to self). Fields: name, slug (unique), description, image, is_featured, meta_title, meta_description.
Brand: Fields: name, slug (unique), logo, description, is_featured.
Product: Fields: category (FK), brand (FK, optional), name, slug (unique), SKU (unique), description, price (DecimalField), discount_price (DecimalField, optional), stock (integer), is_active, is_low_stock (BooleanField), created_at, updated_at, meta_title, meta_description.
ProductImage: Fields: product (FK), image, alt_text, is_featured (BooleanField).
ProductVariant: Allows multiple attributes (e.g., Size, Color). Fields: product (FK), name (e.g., "Size"), value (e.g., "XL"), price_override (DecimalField, optional), stock (integer).
[NEW] 
cart/models.py
Cart: Fields: user (FK, optional for anonymous checkout), session_key (char, optional), created_at, updated_at.
CartItem: Fields: cart (FK), product (FK), variant (FK, optional), quantity (positive integer).
Coupon: Fields: code (unique, uppercase), discount_type (Percentage/Fixed Amount/Free Shipping), value (DecimalField), min_purchase_amount (DecimalField), start_date, end_date, active (BooleanField), usage_limit (integer), times_used (integer).
[NEW] 
orders/models.py
Order: Fields: user (FK, optional), order_number (unique string), status (choices: Pending, Confirmed, Packed, Shipped, Out for Delivery, Delivered, Cancelled, Returned, Refunded), shipping_address (JSONField or FK to snapshot address), payment_method (COD/Stripe/Razorpay), payment_status (Pending/Paid/Failed), subtotal, discount, shipping_charge, total, coupon (FK to Coupon, optional), tracking_number, created_at, updated_at.
OrderItem: Fields: order (FK), product (FK), variant (FK, optional), quantity, price (DecimalField).
[NEW] 
payments/models.py
Transaction: Fields: order (FK), gateway (Stripe/Razorpay), transaction_id (unique string), amount (DecimalField), status (Success/Failed/Refunded), raw_response (JSONField), created_at.
[NEW] 
reviews/models.py
Review: Fields: product (FK), user (FK), rating (integer, 1-5), comment (text), is_verified_purchase (BooleanField), is_approved (BooleanField), helpful_votes (integer), created_at.
ReviewImage: Fields: review (FK), image.
[NEW] 
wishlist/models.py
Wishlist: Fields: user (OneToOne), products (ManyToManyField to Product).
[NEW] 
notifications/models.py
Notification: Fields: user (FK), notification_type (Order/Shipping/Promotion), title, message, link, is_read (BooleanField), created_at.
2. API Design (Django REST Framework)
All APIs will be documentable and return standard JSON formats. We will secure endpoints using JWT (rest_framework_simplejwt).

Endpoints List
POST /api/auth/register/ - Registration of custom user.
POST /api/auth/login/ - Login and returns JWT token.
GET/PUT /api/accounts/profile/ - Retreive/update user profile.
GET /api/products/ - Products catalog with filters (category, brand, price range, etc.) and search suggestions.
GET /api/products/{id}/ - Product details including variants and reviews.
GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/cart/ - Full cart operations.
POST /api/cart/apply-coupon/ - Validates and applies promo code to active cart.
POST /api/orders/checkout/ - Places an order, validates inventory, triggers payment gateways.
POST /api/payments/webhook/stripe/ & post /api/payments/webhook/razorpay/ - Live webhook handling.
POST /api/products/{id}/review/ - Post verified purchase rating/review.
3. UI/UX & Tailwind Design Plan
We will create a premium Responsive layout featuring:

Global Base Layout (base.html): Includes Google Fonts (Inter + Outfit), FontAwesome, sticky responsive header with animated cart badge, responsive search bar, and custom language/currency switcher.
Color Palette: Ultra-premium Slate/Indigo dark & light modes. Dark mode will transition seamlessly (dark:bg-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100).
Home Page: Hero carousel with smooth slide transitions, categories slider, trending products grid, and interactive newsletter forms.
Product Listing & Filtering: Side dynamic filtering sidebar (slide-out on mobile) using AJAX to dynamically load catalog contents without full page refresh.
Product Detail: Multi-image gallery with hover zoom, variant selectors (changing variant automatically adjusts price), reviews listing, and question/answer section.
Checkout Wizard: Clean multi-step visual bar (Address -> Shipping -> Payment -> Success).
Admin Dashboard: Full analysis dashboard displaying sales reports, revenue graphs, and user registrations using Chart.js.
4. Celery, Redis, and Caching Tasks
Redis will act as both Django caching backend and Celery message broker.

Cache Product Catalog: Product lists and detail responses will be cached to ensure sub-100ms response times.
Celery Tasks:
send_verification_email_task: Sends verification email asynchronously.
send_order_confirmation_task: Dispatches transactional HTML emails and SMS logs.
check_low_stock_alert_task: Daily inventory scan checking for products below threshold and notifying admins.
expire_unused_carts_task: Periodic cleanup of stale guest carts.
